author: Inside Edition
description: A dozen holiday puppies got a Hollywood ending, literally, thanks to a Hollywood star. "Clueless" actor Alicia Silverstone noticed their pregnant mother was on a list to be euthanized. She stepped in to help, and was able to connect mama, named Noel, to the Helen Woodward Animal Center in southern California. In the center's care, Noel gave birth to a dozen festively named puppies: Drummer, Piper, Lord, Lady, Maid, Swan, Goose, Ring, Calling Bird, French Hen, Turtle Dove and Partridge.
title: Alicia Silverstone Helps Rescue Pregnant Dog Named Noel From Kill Shelter

author: Inside Edition
description: Doctors in the Netherlands say they've developed another tool to help premature babies in their fight for survival. This artificial womb is meant to replicate the experience of being in utero. It's called AquaWomb. They say the key to making it work is to prevent the fetus from breathing while being transferred from the uterus to the AquaWomb. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Doctors Create Artificial Womb To Help Premature Babies Grow Stronger
